- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper mentions the use of "intelligent" PI controllers, which could potentially involve AI techniques. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper involves simulations of the proposed control method, which could fall under the scope of computational engineering. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): Microgrids are considered an emerging technology in the field of power systems, and the paper specifically focuses on control methods for microgrids. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): While not the main focus of the paper, the proposed control method could involve software engineering aspects such as implementation and testing.
